<LessonData>
  
  <Lesson id="1">
    <Title>Basics of Kenematics: Velocity and Speed</Title>
    <Description>
      Speed is the change in position of an obect. It is measured in m/s and defined as &#x0394;x/&#x0394;t, change in 
      position over change in time.&#x0a;In Calculus, it is the derivative of position.&#x0a;The difference between velocity
      and speed is that speed describes the rate of change in position of an object, regardless of it's direction, velocity
      however, takes direction into account.
    </Description>
    
    <SimData>
      <Ellipse id="0">
        <xPos>10</xPos>
        <yPos>20</yPos>
        <radius>2</radius>
        <ARGBColor>
          <a>255</a>
          <r>255</r>
          <g>087</g>
          <b>051</b>
        </ARGBColor>
        <Velocity>
          <v>0</v>
          <angle>0</angle>
          <xV>10</xV>
          <yV>00</yV>
        </Velocity>
        <mass>1</mass>
        <elasticity>1</elasticity>
      </Ellipse>
      
      <Ellipse id="1">
